			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In response to what I want to see, I the steps that have been taken so far, but I think that the Bounty should definatley be able to attack the Hunter, thats what make some marks so elusive, and will make some of the less experienced hunters think twice about taking some contracts against players.  I also do not think that targets of a bounty should know who is after them, thats the advantage of being the Hunter, and not the Hunted.  In addition to this, I don't know for sure how the contract system is set up right now, but I think that contracts should not be limited to one hunter,  if there is a big bounty out on someone, I think it would be appropriate for there to be 2 or 3 hunters in competition for the same payoff (alla Darth Vader in Empire Strikes back).  I mean it makes sense that if someone if notorious enough to get a large bounty places on their head, that it would draw more attention that one hunter.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
