			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I belive all the ideas here are good but this is what i think should happen
<br />

<br />
When a bounty hunter fights his bounty they should have specialised weapons that give them an advantage, being NPC or PVP (a posion darts, a controled bomb or a robot) this should give them defenant advantag. Now i have played on a PvP server with EQ and most times a player gets attacked when they are at thier weakest. So i would say that yes the hunted should beable to fight back and get support form only member in his/her group (if grouping is planned) forcing the hunter to select a proper time to attack and not to just fly in when he finds the target. I also feel there should be ways for the hunter to find out some needful information about thier target before taking the contract ie abilities, levels, possably faction and location of player.
<br />

<br />
I see two problems the hunters should not beable to be attacked all the time only while attacking. My solution to this is before a hunter can attack they should have to tell the game they are attacking (a command) when that happenes they are open to any attack from grouped members. Also starting a clock to give them a time limit to finish the attack when the time runs out they loose the contract. This will force the hunter to be sneeky and if the hunted knows what is going on for what ever reason they can protect thier partner by creating a sting. The next problem is the logging aspect they may go and hide (teleport) and then log this would not be fare to the bounty hunter. Oh and another problem what if the hunted characture only plays like 5 hours a month (new chracture, bussy month).
