			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am not sure whether there is something that you lot know that I dont, but I do not think sqewing everything in favour of the bounty hunter is on at all.
<br />
A bounty hunter should only be awarded contracts that gives both players an even chance of vanquishing the other, but not necessarily all the time ie at times one will have an advantage (bounty hunter gets first shot) and at other times the hunted will retain the advantage. (being grouped with others) It is the bounty hunters perogative to find the optimum time to attack.
<br />
If having a bounty on your head is supposed to be a 'punishment' to discourage behaviour that is supposed to be discouraged, then the other posters suggestions are probably more valid, However I wouldnt necesarily call bounty hunting a 'noble' proffesion either.
<br />

<br />
Also having to find the optimum time to attack will add a lot of depth with trailing - possibly for several hours before the perfect 'hit spot' can be found. 
<br />
I also like the idea of multiple hunters after a single target. This could add great depth - if these rivals can perhaps duke it out amongst themselves, and generally sabotage things for each other. They are also generating 'interest' whereby the hunted may be alerted to a hunter presence in the same zone, possibly even turning the tables. 
<br />

<br />
No matter what is decided the contract ought to be brought to a halt by the death of one party by the other. This would stop any ugly scenes of vengefull non consensual killing, or repeated ganks.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
