			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=1231&amp;sid=258b55b1d6859e38d7cd9bfe2d77254d#1231"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Tue Oct 15, 2002 9:11 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: Bounty Hunting - Your thoughts</span></td>
				<td valign="top" align="right" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=1231&amp;sid=258b55b1d6859e38d7cd9bfe2d77254d"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">&lt;&lt;&lt;  Should victims be able to attack their bounty hunter or should they only be able to attack in self-defense (Bounty Hunter must make first attack as per rules of a challenger of a duel)?  &gt;&gt;&gt;
<br />

<br />
To answer this question, the second question must be answered first.
<br />

<br />
&lt;&lt;&lt;  Should victims know who their bounty hunter is?  &gt;&gt;&gt;
<br />

<br />
The victim should not automatically know that they are being hunted.  The player may suspect that their character is being hunted, but there should not be a little warning light going off telling the player that their character is being hunted.  How realistic is that?  If a character manages to find out that they are being hunted, it should be possible for them to find out who the hunter is.  It's called role-playing.  Hire a slicer to hack into the bounty hunter database (or whatever) to get the information.  Bribe a member of the bounty hunter faction to tell you.  Creative players should be able to think up thousands of ways to find out.
<br />

<br />
That being said, if a character finds out that they are being hunted AND they find out who the hunter is, they absolutely should be able to attack first.
<br />

<br />
&lt;&lt;&lt;  What would you like to see in the Bounty Hunter system?   &gt;&gt;&gt;
<br />

<br />
Informants.  I would like to see NPC informants who can tell a character they are being hunted, for a fee, of course.  I would also like to see informants who tell the bounty hunter "I last saw that person on Corellia" or whatever.
<br />

<br />
&lt;&lt;&lt;  What do you think would cause problems in the Bounty Hunter system?  &gt;&gt;&gt;
<br />

<br />
If multiple hunters can accept the same hunt, then teaming up must be monitored closely.  There is no reason they shouldn't be able to work together, but there needs to be mechanism in place to moderate it.  If one bounty hunter decides to screw the hunters that helped him, then they need to have some sort of recourse to get their share of the reward.  Maybe they should be able to put a price on his head?  Maybe hunters should be licensed, and if a hunter is reported as having kept the whole pot, his license should be revoked.
<br />

<br />
Those are some of my thoughts.....</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
